	<p>As someone who is looking forward to WoW, I am really worried about the security measures they utilize for the game.  Heck, they've already had a leak of the 'alpha' code hit the internet and it took 3 days for a group of programmers to build the existing world based from that alpha.  With that much code already out on the internet, how tough will it be to find that cracks in it?  <br />
<br />
Quiinn, 65 Barbarian Shaman</p>
	
	
	
	
	
