	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I have my hopes for WoW.  Frankly,  there are security measures taken in MMORPGs that are not done in games like Diablo II.  For one, there are far more servers, and need for constant support.  You really can't compare it with Battle.net.<br />
<br />
But all that aside, I just have one thing to point out...<br />
<br />
I am sick of everyone always putting a "Griefer" in the 10-12 year age group.  Thats ALL I EVER HEAR.  Hes a griefer?  Must be a middle school child.  Must be a 12 year old.  <br />
<br />
Lets face it.  Most griefers are probably - and i'm not proud of this - in my age group.  College students.  And you know you can't deny that.  If they aren't college students, then they are probably older people with harsh jobs that get burned out IRL.<br />
<br />
I'm not going to pass judgements on WoW any more then I do on SOE for Gates of Discord.  Theres NO possible way to know anything about either of them right now.<br />
<br />
There are some good points, yes, but there are bad ones, and oversights.  It's a good post overall, but it's hardly comprehensive about ANY of the topics he covered.  (Griefers are NOT rare in EQ and they are NOT often hunted down.  Not on blue servers, not on the PVP servers)<br />
<br />
But, I have to go, so I will leave you with this final word.  And I think you'll find, after reading it, that it gets harder and harder to argue with me.  <br />
<br />
Spoon!<br />
<br />
~Detton</p>
	
	
	
	
	
