	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>yes plenty of griefers are older too...  I used to have some friends who were heavy PK in UO and they were mostly Adults.<br />
<br />
Blizzard games do appeal to a broad age group.<br />
<br />
But one very important point to keep in mind, with Blizzard specifically DII and WC3 ON LINE - those are FREE services all you need is to have bought the game, no monthly recurring:  so you will get:<br />
a)  younger players because there is no monthly payment.<br />
b)  people who are more reckless and have less concern for the consequences of their actions because they have less at stake in terms of not investing that monthly fee.<br />
<br />
I am very much hoping that WoW isnt like so much of UO was, or the stories I hear about DII, or what I have seen in WC3.  It's hardly the best article but I do VERY much agree with the general sentiment behind it about the importance of community.</p>
	
	
	
