</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>This is what I have been saying for months, since i started playing everquest even. The attractive part of Everquest is the strategy. Period. The people who play it more than two weeks play it for the strategy. The twisting of songs, the art of debuffing, perfectly timed nukes, disciplines, feigns, DoTs, it's all strategy. And that's what makes it so much fun.<br />
<br />
I know zero hardcore players who haven't tapped into the strategy part of Everquest. Even those who refuse to join raiding guilds where the strategy is most self-evident, do hard difficulty LDoN adventures, extremely risky group combinations, and record-breaking solos. <br />
<br />
Its the trend that is everywhere. Warcraft III is breaking the mold the same way Everquest is, but in the opposite direction. Warcraft III is an RTS that introduced RPG elements. Everquest is an RPG that introduced RTS elements. <br />
<br />
I guess to summarize, I hope dearly that World of Warcraft keeps a deep level of strategy, and the proverbial levelling treadmill is done away with.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
