	<!-- message -->
	<p>Just a couple of things about WoW from someone who isn't really a fan of any mmorpg (as a fanboi anyway)..<br />
<br />
The "security" issues for WoW are moot..  The reason is, mmorg's use a client/server protocol where as Diablo is a peer to peer game.<br />
<br />
Sony/Verant didn't have any exp in the mmorpg market when they launched EQ.  Look where it is.<br />
<br />
Blizzard has a track record for making complete, and addictive games.<br />
<br />
The look of WoW is amazing (from game play movies and screenshots).  This will draw alot of people at first, but you are right, some will return from where they came.<br />
<br />
The PWNJOO crowd?  that is what ignore if for, you don't have to play with them, or let them in your groups.<br />
<br />
All online games have griefers of some sort...<br />
They either PK lowbies..<br />
Price gouge..<br />
Kill steal..<br />
the list goes on, but all online games have them..<br />
<br />
The PWNJOO crowd is very much apart of EQ, it's just that the older more rounded guilds don't ever deal with them, they are there, I can vouch for it as a recently new member (2 months) to everquest.<br />
<br />
I, personally, picked up EQ, because i was sick of what Mythic was doing to DAoC, and had no plan of sticking around.  I'm going to play WoW when it comes out, and i'm neither a fanboi nor in the PWNJOO crowd.<br />
<br />
I play with a group (10-20) friends, and we are just going to go out and have fun.<br />
<br />
Give the game a chance, or don't, it is ultimately your decision, however, this game (WoW) isn't being "catered" for the "younger" crowd of online gaming.<br />
<br />
Some players from D2/WC3/SC will come over, but I honestly feel when most of the "cheaters" figure out that their isn't an "easy" way, they will go back to map hacking D2.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
