	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>EQ is NOT hard.  It does not take any extraordinary "skill" to do well at EQ - other than patience.  I have hardly played in the last year - NEVER been on a PoP raid, never been to LDoN, and NEVER played a casting class of any kind past level 4 (besides shaman).  <br />
<br />
I played around in the GoD beta - and played a 65 version of almost every class in a group or raid.  I have no experience playing a cleric, or enchanter, or necro, or SK, but every group I was in had no idea i was a "noob".  Its all pretty simple.  There is not that much to it.<br />
<br />
One thing I will grant you - you can do stupid stuff - like train your group - and hurt your group.  But as long as you have some common sense, and are not a moron - you should figure out how to play fairly easy.  I would venture to say that 99% of folks who can operate a computer could play EQ no troubles.<br />
<br />
If you think EQ is "hard" - or requires "skill" - I suppose I owe you a compliment for being able to find and read this thread.  I should probably give you a cookie if you can actually figure out how to post <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
	
	
