	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Playing EQ doesn't require much skill.  After all you do what you do so many times that it becomes pretty routine stuff.<br />
<br />
But EQ, when I first played it, did have one aspect that was hard - deciding where to go and what to kill to progress by gaining both experience and by getting gear from drops.  I used to spend hours researching what my options were and deciding how and when I could attempt them.<br />
<br />
That's part of what I hated about EverRaid: a casual player now just farms pp to buy his gear in the bazaar, a raider just turns up wherever the man says the raid is tonight.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
