	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Love this article.<br />
<br />
I'm really looking forward to WoW.  My only real fear is that it will be too WC3 and D2 like.  While I enjoyed both games, they both got old because of the same things.  <br />
<br />
a) The griefing in these games is insane.  As a beginner in WC3, I would hate people just crushing me, and they would say things like "Have you ever played this before?".  At level 1, why is everyone so good in WC3??? <br />
b) There was only one path for each character.  In D2 if you had a barbarian you ended up a WW machine.  If you played a Necro you ended up a revive corpse machine.  A little creativity could go far here.  In WC3, you had a set build order and you stuck to it, no realy ingenuity there.<br />
<br />
I'm hoping WoW will be better, but I won't be surprised if it isn't.</p>
	
	
	
