	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>E.Q. is as hard as you make it, <br />
if you think playing a chanter is easy then take a 30ish lvl chanter into castle MM and charm up the Dark huntress deep inside and solo with that monster as a pet. if you can pull that off I will give you kudos for your skills. if you can mez/tash mobs on a raid, grats you are perfectly normal.<br />
if you can keep 6 mobs mez'd while your group ganks the 7th and not lose a player and not lose mez on any of them, while calling targets for the tank to kill next. you get kudos, if you pop off an ae mez and scream evac your just plain old normal.<br />
<br />
of you can duo a rogue/monk for exp off of red mobs with ultra crappy gear and do so with minimal deaths and a decent kill rate you get some credit for understanding the game, if you instead spend hours in pok lfg with your rogue monk duo you are just plain old normal.<br />
<br />
eq is one game that will allow you to truly push the limits of what you can do with what you are given. of course its easy to do baxic crowd control with a chanter, duh thats their primary role. you only know who shines as a chanter when the **** really hits the fan and the come out clean on the other side with a look that says "what you guys were worried?<br />
<br />
the fact that most of us can play any class at an acceptable lvl of skill on a raid doesnt say jack. most of use are 65 and have been for some time, most of us have at least 2 toons that are 50+, most of us have spent literally MONTHS of our lives playing this game. if you can spend that much time at something like eq and NOT pick up the other class's basics your a moron. <br />
the only true test of skill would come with playing the class in its role in its most stressing type of game play.<br />
<br />
how many of you have done the rogue solo run in PoH for the epic drop?  (pre sos)<br />
or solo'd in a place or mobs that you never thought you could handle with your shaman and trusty Dog Dog? <br />
most of us are accomplished shaman, some are acomplished at other classes as well. but admit it, you have all met that Paly/druid/ranger/chanter/bard/rogue that just amazed you with the skills they displayed at the time. <br />
raids are a piss poor example of skill displays, there are dozens of people to make up for mistakes and little for individuals to do 90% of the time.<br />
<br />
as a shaman I think my personal best night for pure raid skill was doing seru with 3 bane rangers and 5 wizzy/mages for most of our dps. I was the only shaman, the only RGC, and of course the only FA. I had to keep seru slowed, malos'd, decay'd, cycle FA on the rangers, handle requests for RGC and slow/malos adds...I worked my ass off that raid and we won. I consider that raid a person victory, there is no way we could have done it without me there and theres only one other shaman (I think) with Rgc in the guild. <br />
<br />
showing up casting malos/slow on the boss mob is something a bot can do.<br />
<br />
what the hell am I rambling about? hell I dont know anymore, but if WoW doesnt allow for the ability to really push the envelope the it fails like most of them do.<br />
<br />
<br />
and *** eq HAS PVP SERVERS! grats daoc blows, in large part to having ONE ruleset for all servers. morons.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
